        public void setResponseHandler(ResponseHandler<T> handler)
        Set a custom handler that will be triggered when the response returns either Success or Fail. You can choose where this info is sent. **Default** is the UIThreadREsponseHandler implementation which runs the appropriate callback on the UI thread.
        Parameters:

      • setStatusHandler

        public void setStatusHandler(ResponseStatusHandler statusHandler)
        By default success is a code in the range of 2xx. Everything else triggers an Error. You can set a handler which will take into account your own custom error codes to determine if the response is a success or fail.

        statusHandler -
